    • Method Detail

      • getCallerPrincipal

        private java.security.Principal getCallerPrincipal​(javax.security.auth.Subject subject)
        Obtains the caller principal from the specified Subject. This method looks for a group called CallerPrincipal and if it finds one it returns the first Principal in the group.
        Parameters:
        subject - the Subject to be inspected.
        Returns:
        the first Principal found in the CallerPrincipal group or null if a caller principal couldn't be found.
